    "This process involves not only decomposing highlevel requests into sub-tasks but also intelligently allocating these tasks based on agent capabilities, environmental context, and resource availability.",
    "Recent progress in task orchestration focuses on two key aspects: task decomposition and task allocation.a) Task Decomposition.",
    "Task decomposition serves as the foundational step in task assignment within IoA systems, where high-level requests are broken down into manageable and executable sub-tasks.",
    "Recent advancements can be categorized into rule-based (or symbolic-based) decomposition and learningbased decomposition approaches.• Rule-based decomposition.",
    "Grounded in the classic divideand-conquer paradigm [108], rule-based methods explicitly parse tasks according to pre-defined schemas or logical structures, enabling fine-grained control over complex objectives."
  ],
